Field,Specification,Description
Asset Universe,EM Currency Pairs,"USD/BRL, USD/MXN, USD/COP, USD/CLP, USD/PEN, USD/TRY, USD/ZAR, USD/RUB (if tradable), USD/ILS, USD/HUF, USD/PLN, USD/CZK, USD/CNH, USD/INR (NDF), USD/IDR (NDF), USD/KRW, USD/MYR (NDF), USD/SGD, USD/PHP, USD/THB, USD/TWD."
Data Type 1,Spot Rate (Mid),Used to track spot moves.
Data Type 2,Implied Volatility,"1-Month ATM Implied Volatility. (While the paper uses 12M and Risk Reversals, 1M ATM is the primary liquid intraday driver)."
Frequency,Spot: 1-MinuteVol: 15-Minute,Spot data must be high frequency. Options markets for EM are less liquid; a 15-minute or 30-minute snapshot of the vol surface is sufficient to capture intraday repricing.

Field,Specification,Description
Asset Universe,Sovereign Bond Futures,US: 10Y Treasury Note Futures (TY)Germany: Euro-Bund Futures (FGBL) & Euro-Schatz (FGBS - for curve)UK: Long Gilt Futures (G)Japan: 10Y JGB Futures (JB)
Data Type,OHLCV Bars,"Close price is used for Momentum calculations (e.g., Price vs Moving Average).Yield implies are needed for Carry (Steepness)."
Frequency,15-Minute,Trend and Carry signals are slower-moving; 15-minute bars filter out noise while retaining intraday responsiveness.
Session,Global,"These markets trade in different time zones. You must normalize data to GMT or capture their respective active trading hours (London, NY, Tokyo)."

Field,Specification,Description
Asset Universe,Cycle Proxies,Copper: HG Futures (High sensitivity to global growth/cycle).Oil: CL Futures (Inflation/Growth input).Equity Vol: VIX Index (Risk aversion proxy).
Data Type,Last Price,"Used as correlation inputs to determine the ""Cycle"" regime."
Frequency,5-Minute,"""Cycle"" assets are volatile; higher frequency is needed to capture rapid shifts in sentiment intraday."

Summary of ALL Required Data Feeds (Merged List)
US Sectors (11 ETFs): For Absorption Ratio (Systemic Risk).

EM Basket (Spot FX, FX Vol, Index Fut, Bond Fut, Bond ETFs): For EM Risk Monitor.

US Credit Term Structure (VCSH, VCIT, VCLT): For Credit Spread Slope/Curvature.

Risk-Free Term Structure (UST Futures 2Y, 5Y, 10Y, 30Y): For Riskless Slope.

Global Sovereigns (Bund, Gilt, JGB Futures): For MS Bond Signals.

Cycle Commodities (Copper, Oil): For Economic Cycle inputs.
